des:
"If you have any problem when you use this skill, you can contact us with email : service@s-butler.com
Amazon Alexa and the S-Butler home products work together to help you control home appliance nice and easy.
You can simply ask Alexa to turn on, turn off or dim the appliance. 
There’s no need to go to the switch to adjust you home appliance - just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo, Echo Dot, Amazon Tap or Echo Show. 
After connecting Alexa to your Tuya Smart products in a few simple steps:
(1). Download our ""S-Butler"" app in android or ios app market;
(2). Register one S-Butlera ccount in our ""S-Butler"" app;
(3). You need to have some S-Butler devices in hand;
(4). Configure these devices in our ""S-Butler"" app and change appropriate name for your devices which will be used in ""S-Butler"" skills;
(5). Download Amazon ""Alexa"" app from android,ios or Amazon app market;
(6). Configure Echo with ""Alexa"" app;
(7). Search ""S-Butler"" skill from the ""Alexa"" app skills category;
(8). Click Enable skill of ""S-Butler"", and you'll be navigated to S-Butler login page;
(9). Input your S-Butler account username and password, you'll be redirect to the success page;
(10). Now all setup is finished. 
You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
“Alexa, turn on bedroom fan""
“Alexa, turn off bedroom fan""
“Alexa, turn on livingroom heater""
“Alexa, turn off livingroom heater""
“Alexa, turn on livingroom air conditioner""
“Alexa, turn off livingroom air conditioner""
“Alexa, set the livingroom air conditioner to 25 degree""

Currently this skill supports products:
smart remote controller,
smart socket, 
smart appliance...."
